Mauritius Commercial Bank Forecasts Economy Will Expand 4.3% This Year

-- B y   K a m l e s h   B h u c k o r y
-- 
2011-06-24T11:58:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-24/mauritius-commercial-bank-forecasts-economy-will-expand-4-3-this-year.html
Mauritius’s economy is expected to
expand by 4.3 percent this year after growing 4.4 percent in
2010, said Mauritius Commercial Bank, the country’s largest
lender by market value.  Unemployment in the Indian Ocean island nation will
probably increase to 8 percent from 7.8 percent, the Port Louis-
based bank said in an e-mailed statement today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kamlesh Bhuckory in Port Louis at 
 kbhuckory@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gordon Bell at 
 gbell16@bloomberg.net  